[1mNAME[0m[m
       ln - make links between files[m
[m
[1mSYNOPSIS[0m[m
       [1mln [22m[[4mOPTION[24m]... [[4m-T[24m] [4mTARGET[24m [4mLINK_NAME[0m[m
       [1mln [22m[[4mOPTION[24m]... [4mTARGET[0m[m
       [1mln [22m[[4mOPTION[24m]... [4mTARGET[24m... [4mDIRECTORY[0m[m
       [1mln [22m[[4mOPTION[24m]... [4m-t[24m [4mDIRECTORY[24m [4mTARGET[24m...[m
[m
[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
       In the 1st form, create a link to TARGET with the name LINK_NAME.  In the 2nd form, create a link to TARGET in[m
       the current directory.  In the 3rd and 4th forms, create links to each TARGET in DIRECTORY.  Create hard links[m
       by  default,  symbolic  links with [1m--symbolic[22m.  By default, each destination (name of new link) should not al‐[m
       ready exist.  When creating hard links, each TARGET must exist.  Symbolic links can hold  arbitrary  text;  if[m
       later resolved, a relative link is interpreted in relation to its parent directory.[m
[m
       Mandatory arguments to long options are mandatory for short options too.[m
[m
       [1m--backup[22m[=[4mCONTROL[24m][m
              make a backup of each existing destination file[m
[m
       [1m-b     [22mlike [1m--backup [22mbut does not accept an argument[m
[m
       [1m-d[22m, [1m-F[22m, [1m--directory[0m[m
              allow  the  superuser  to  attempt to hard link directories (note: will probably fail due to system re‐[m
              strictions, even for the superuser)[m
[m
